            <gmd:supplementalInformation>
                <gco:CharacterString>A Synchrotron Radiation Based Study of BP Deepwater Horizon Oil Spill Samples A. BP Oil FTIR Spectra 1. BP Control Burn 2. BP NWF Oil 3. BP Oil 1800 to 650 4. BP Oil 3800 to 2500 5. BP Oil 4000 to 650 6. BP Riser Oil 7. weathered oil 10 miles from source|The X-ray techniques used were X-ray absorption spectroscopy which provides information about speciation, that is, how an element is present rather than total concentration; X-ray diffractometry which identifies the phases present; small and wide angle X-ray scattering which determines structures ranging from microstructure on the colloidal length scale to the crystal structure at the atomic length scale. Parameters include structure, chemical composition, and physical properties.|Experimental lab measurements using synchrotron-based techniques of oil samples. X-ray absorption spectroscopy X-ray diffractometry X-Ray tomography Infrared spectroscopy|All the data were collected in ASCII format. If image files were obtained, they are in *.tif or *.bmp. Some of the reduced data in graphical form is shown in *.wmf form. This can be easily imported into any word processing program such as Word. X-ray absorption spectroscopy data were reduced with freely available software Athena with Demeter (http://bruceravel.github.io/demeter/). The project files from this software are included in the dataset.||</gco:CharacterString>
